    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://phoenix.craigslist.org/evl/sec/6043894652.html"></div>
        </div>
Bolt Security Guard Services, one of Arizona's leading independently-owned and operated security firms, is hiring armed and unarmed security officers in the Phoenix area. No experience is necessary.<br>
<br>
Before applying, please make sure you meet the following requirements:<br>
<br>
-You're at least 18 years old (21 for armed officers)<br>
-You possess a VALID Arizona armed or unarmed DPS guard card<br>
<br>
Bolt Security Guard Services is hiring officers for work sites, access control, patrol and alarm response, schools, administration, and much more. We're also offering a sign-on bonus of $100 for full-time employees that remain with the company for at least three weeks. In addition, we have a referral program that lets employees earn up to $100 for referring a qualifying friend or family member that is hired for a full-time position and remains with the company for at least one month!<br>
<br>
Positions available include:<br>
-Patrolman (full-time, $13/hour, Wednesday through Sunday 3rd shift)<br>
-General unarmed guard (full-time/part-time with flexible hours, $10+/hour depending on experience, no computer skills necessary)<br>
-Armed guard (part-time, $14/hour, Monday and Tuesday 3rd shift)<br>
-Event guards (hiring immediately for large-scale event this weekend, 12-hour shifts, 1st and 2nd shift)<br>
-School patrolman (full-time/part-time with flexible hours, Central Phoenix area, 2nd and 3rd shifts, $10+/hour depending on experience, must have valid AZ driver's license)<br>
<br>
Don't have any security experience? We'll provide it. Learn from seasoned industry veterans within our company structure.<br>
<br>
Essential skills guards should have:<br>
<br>
-Mastery of the English language in speaking, reading, and writing<br>
-Proficient computer skills<br>
-Ability to provide superior customer service, including punctuality, courtesy, and respect<br>
-Ability to follow written or verbal instructions from supervisory staff<br>
<br>
Bolt Security Guard Services is proud to be an equal-opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will be considered for employment without regard to race, religion, gender, disability, or protected status (veteran or otherwise). We are committed to providing reasonable accommodation to applicants with disabilities.<br>
    </section>

